{"sequence":17,"timestamp":"2026-04-11T17:27:43.951036292Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-f99b994c","body":"`src/cli/run.rs:2035-2059` still leaves a stale-state window after SIGTERM. The wrapper now calls `reconcile_signal_interruption()` only after the backend future finishes or after `RUN_STOP_GRACE_PERIOD` expires, but it does not persist the interrupted snapshot or remove `run.pid` when the signal is first observed. If a supervisor or a second signal kills the orchestrator during that wait, the project is still left in `Running` with a live `run.pid`, which is the durability gap this bead is meant to close. Persist the interrupted state (or an equivalent durable handoff marker) before entering the grace-period wait, then let later completion reconcile forward if the run actually finishes cleanly.","dedup_key":"123b84d43267e02bffa51a227fec32d79d131e206aff091d7aeb3c20d05dffc6","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260411170802","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":18,"timestamp":"2026-04-11T17:27:43.960074455Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-1-f208e741","body":"`src/cli/run.rs:2414-2434` makes stale backend cleanup unsafe under PID/PGID reuse. The old `is_backend_process_alive()` guard was removed so orphaned same-process-group children can be killed after the leader exits, but the replacement code now sends `kill(-pid, SIGKILL)` as long as the record contains authoritative identity fields, without first proving that numeric PID/PGID still belongs to the original backend leader. If that leader exited and the PID/PGID was reused, `run stop`/stale recovery can kill an unrelated process group or process. Add a reuse-safe validation strategy before signaling `-pid` (or refuse cleanup when that guarantee cannot be established).","dedup_key":"271ba5375979026cd5c900379eee9a50b442a408a6a6298e9d8988b64e83e4d3","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260411170802","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
