{"sequence":73,"timestamp":"2026-04-11T18:39:35.049927036Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-368d80ff","body":"Fix the SIGTERM handoff so it does not append a durable `run_failed` journal event before the engine future finishes. In `src/cli/run.rs:2098-2103` and `src/cli/run.rs:2146-2175`, the wrapper persists interruption state via `mark_running_run_interrupted()` and then still allows the engine future to continue. If the engine later reaches its normal failure path, it appends another terminal event using its stale in-memory `seq` counter at `src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:5987-6000`, which can write a duplicate or out-of-order journal sequence and corrupt `journal.ndjson`.","dedup_key":"6a548ec6722da13ce60e12dce56c9340750749e44a74f6cfe8cd1652c8332b4d","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260411170802","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":74,"timestamp":"2026-04-11T18:39:35.059446384Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-4-0cad23f0","body":"Do not treat every dead tracked backend leader as a hard cleanup failure. `kill_stale_backend_process_group()` now errors immediately when `is_backend_process_alive(record)` is false (`src/cli/run.rs:2622-2626`), and stale recovery invokes that path before it can repair the snapshot (`src/cli/run.rs:2793-2795`). If a backend already exited cleanly but its `active-processes.json` entry survived a crash or forced stop, `run resume` on a stale Running snapshot fails even though there is nothing left to kill.","dedup_key":"a27d5d8a9e981adc5adabcc6a775301d762f49ce5cdacf263a1cc85a2bd6bf54","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260411170802","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
